latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Who better than the charismatic  @varundvn to celebrate the magic of movies!? As a film buff myself, this has to be one of the most special shoots I’ve planned. Shooting with the actor in a cinema hall, talking all about his love and passion for films, and going all out crazy in between with the best team in the world… happy shoots are the best ones! 

#respost
@lifestyleasiaindia @lsa.arena 

After a lull of two years, movie business in India is finally back on its feet. With several films performing well at the box-office, it seems like the worst is over and it’s time to go #backtothecinemas. And celebrating the arrival of the good times with us is one of the most bankable and popular actors of the country, Varun Dhawan (@varundvn). #LifestyleAsiaIndia's March cover star, Dhawan lives and breathes movies. In an exclusive, we shot with him inside a cinema hall and sat down with him to talk about his love for films, the pandemic and what he thinks is the future of showbiz. Stay tuned!

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There’s a lot to learn from @karanjohar. One of it being self love. When I spoke to him after this shoot about his recent style metamorphosis, he said, “My love for fashion is unapologetic, unconventional but it is what I love. I’m going to be 50 in May and I do not want to do things that don't make me happy and I've stopped caring about what everyone thinks.” 

Life is anyway too short to wear boring clothes and here he is, serving major looks during our latest cover shoot. ✨

#repost @lifestyleasiaindia

latestPosts.caption:
Esquire India’s Editor, Rahul Gangwani (@rahulgangs_) attended the ZEGNA (@zegna) Summer 2026 showcase at the iconic Dubai Opera, transformed into Villa Zegna for the occasion. 

Alessandro Sartori’s (@alessandrosartoriofficial) collection presented a refined vision of modern luxury, with sun-washed silks, linen Shetland and fluid silhouettes that balanced innovation with timeless elegance. The evening was set to a soulful live performance by James Blake, adding to the atmosphere of quiet grandeur.

#EsquireIndia #Zegna #ZegnaSS26 #VillaZegna

This one is a nod to all things built to last - swipe to read more.

latestPosts.caption:
A special one! 🩷 

I’ve met @pachojaipur on multiple occasions and have always admired his quiet confidence. His personal style too is effortless, modern yet deep-rooted. In the last decade, he has done something remarkable. He has taken the deeply-soaked-in-culture Jaipur and given it a new coat. Pacho understands the past must not only be preserved but also reimagined and made appealing to the newer generation. The kind of renaissance Jaipur has had in the last few years deserves a case study. And we had to celebrate that! 

Sawai Padmanabh Singh in all his glory for the third edition of @esquireindia! 

——

latestPosts.caption:
The charming @vickykaushal09 is, in many ways, a reflection of what Esquire stands for: a man of talent, integrity, and effortless style. But beyond the craft and the success, he’s also one of the nicest guys I have come across. My dear friend and ace photographer @rohanshrestha, who often works with Vicky, once described him as “a warm hug in human form.” I couldn’t agree more. There’s an ease to him, a genuine warmth that makes him instantly likable, not just as an actor but as a person. And as always shooting with him was a delight!

Here’s Vicky Kaushal for the second issue of @esquireindia. Brilliantly photographed by @ashishisshah, styled impeccably by @vijendra.bhardwaj and interviewed by @mayuxkh.

#VickyKaushal #Esquire #EsquireIndia #Chhaava #Vicky

latestPosts.caption:
And so it begins! The first edition of Esquire India is here. The DNA of the magazine is ‘man at his best’ and who better than @hrithikroshan to embody that ethos? 

The first issue is packed with style, substance and stalwarts… can’t wait to share more with you in the coming days. 

#Repost @esquireindia 

The myth, the man, the moment – presenting Hrithik Roshan (@hrithikroshan) on the cover of Esquire India’s inaugural edition.

Twenty-five years ago, his debut film billed him as Indian cinema’s next big superstar. Title after title followed: Greek God, Box-Office magnet and more. Roshan has lived up to each with élan, cementing his legend.

At Esquire, we celebrate the ‘man at his best,’ and truly, is there anyone better suited to that term than Hrithik Roshan?
